  "text": "ArangoDB AQL Query Execution Pipeline: The query execution follows a five-stage pipeline in the C++ codebase:\n\n1. **Parsing Stage** - arangod/Aql/Parser.cpp (Parser class): The AQL query string is parsed using the Parser class, which uses a lexer (Aql/tokens.ll) and parser grammar to build an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST). The Parser::parse() method orchestrates this process.\n\n2. **Optimization Stage** - arangod/Aql/Optimizer.cpp (Optimizer class): The Optimizer class takes the AST from the Parser and applies optimization rules to transform it into an ExecutionPlan. The Optimizer::createPlans() method creates one or more optimized execution plans from the initial plan, selecting the best one based on cost estimation.\n\n3. **Execution Engine Setup** - arangod/Aql/ExecutionEngine.cpp (ExecutionEngine class): The ExecutionEngine class instantiates the execution plan into a tree of ExecutionBlock objects. The static method ExecutionEngine::instantiateFromPlan() creates the engine from the optimized plan, managing memory and coordination of execution blocks.\n\n4. **Execution Blocks** - arangod/Aql/ExecutionBlock.cpp (ExecutionBlock class): ExecutionBlock is the base class for all execution blocks (ScatterBlock, GatherBlock, TableScanBlock, etc.). Each block implements specific operations in the query execution plan. ExecutionBlockImpl.tpp contains template implementations for different block types.\n\n5. **Storage Engine Interface** - arangod/RocksDBEngine/RocksDBCollection.cpp (RocksDBCollection class): RocksDBCollection provides the storage engine interface for actual data retrieval. It implements methods like getAllIterator(), getAnyIterator(), and lookupKey() that access the RocksDB key-value store.\n\n6. **Transaction Management** - arangod/Transaction/Manager.cpp (Manager class): The Manager class tracks and manages TransactionState instances for queries. It handles transaction lifecycle (creation, expiration, cleanup) and ensures ACID properties during query execution. Transaction::Methods provides the transaction API used by ExecutionBlocks to perform DML operations.\n\nThe execution flow: Query String → Parser → AST → Optimizer → ExecutionPlan → ExecutionEngine → ExecutionBlocks → RocksDBCollection (via Transaction/Manager for ACID compliance)"
}

